net.zerobandwidth.android.lib.nonsense

Interface NonsenseGenerator

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    BuildertextJavaclass, NonsenseBuilder, NonsenseShipOrPub

    public interface NonsenseGenerator
    This interface provides a specification for a "nonsense generator" — a class which generates a fully-formed sentence from randomly-chosen words.
    Since:
    zerobandwidth-net/android 0.0.1 (#7)

    • Nested Class Summary

    • Method Detail

      • setContext

        NonsenseGenerator setContext(android.content.Context ctx)
        Sets the context in which string resources can be fetched. If this context has not yet been set, then the class will not be able to fetch string resources to assemble the nonsense string. Implementations of this interface should also provide a constructor which sets this context upfront.
        Parameters:
        ctx - the context in which string resources are available
        Returns:
        (fluid)

      • getString

        java.lang.String getString()
        Generates the nonsense string. The algorithm for creating the string is implementation-dependent.
        Returns:
        a fully-formed sentence from randomly-selected words
